17/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The dispute between Greece and Macedonia on the latter's constitutional name could be resolved by the end of this year, the Greek daily To Vima reported on Wednesday (16 February). The newspaper quoted a ranking UN diplomat as saying the latest round of consultations suggested an improved outlook for reaching a settlement.
In other news, local media is reporting that outgoing Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos has called for immediate action to root out corruption. In remarks Tuesday, Stephanopoulos expressed deep concern about recent scandals involving the judicial sector and the Greek Orthodox Church. (Utrinski Vesnik - 17/02/05; A1 TV, Makfax, To Vima, MPA - 16/02/05) 
